# Projects Consumer Layer Rules

## Role
This directory contains business consumer projects.
These projects consume the FQL design system and should not redefine it.

## Source of truth
- Shared primitives belong in `../ai-agent-design-system/components/ui/*`.
- Shared semantic wrappers belong in `../ai-agent-design-system/components/fql/*`.
- Shared token mapping belongs in `../ai-agent-design-system/app/globals.css`.
- Registry-related assets belong in `../ai-agent-design-system`.

## Consumption behavior
- Always check whether the needed UI already exists upstream before creating local components.
- Prefer consuming existing design-system components over rebuilding them locally.
- If a missing pattern looks reusable across multiple projects, propose promoting it into the design system first.
- Keep business assembly local, keep reusable abstractions upstream.

## Styling behavior
- Prefer semantic tokens and existing design-system styling conventions.
- Do not hardcode hex colors, radius values, or shadow values when upstream semantic tokens already solve the need.
- Do not create a parallel theme system without explicit approval.

## Implementation behavior
- State the target project before multi-file edits.
- Provide a short plan before changing multiple files.
- List changed files after implementation.
- Explicitly mark anything reusable as a promotion candidate for the design system.

## Do not
- Do not recreate `components/ui/*` inside business projects.
- Do not recreate `components/fql/*` locally unless it is intentionally temporary and clearly marked.
- Do not move business-specific page logic into the design system.
